description.default: You are standing on the main dock of Styrm's Delta. The air is heavy with the smell of salt, fish, and tar. Gulls cry overhead as sailors and dockhands shout and haul crates. The wide docks, slick with seawater, stretch out to the east, west, and further north along a long pier. The city gate is to the south.

objects.description: A sailor with weathered skin and a coil of rope over their shoulder. They look too busy to talk.
objects.name: a busy sailor

objects.description: Stacks of wooden crates stamped with various guild sigils.
objects.name: crates

description.default: You are at the end of a long wooden pier. A large merchant cog, 'The Golden Lady', is moored here, its crew loading cargo. The main dock is to the south.

objects.description: A large merchant cog, its hull scarred from long voyages. A wooden ramp leads up to its deck.
objects.name: The Golden Lady

description.default: The dock continues to the east, running alongside a row of tall, narrow warehouses. The main dock is to the west.

objects.description: A large, barred door to a warehouse. It is locked.
objects.name: warehouse door

description.default: This part of the dock seems less busy. Nets are strung out to dry, and the smell of fish is particularly strong here. The main dock is to the east.

objects.description: Large nets, damp and smelling of fish, are draped over barrels to dry.
objects.name: fishing nets
